# TD CLI

Use the td cli to view and edit the project tasks.

# Usage

td <COMMAND>

Commands:
list - list all todo items [aliases: l, ls]
add - add a new todo item or subtask [aliases: a]
check - mark an item as completed [aliases: c]
delete - delete an item [aliases: d, rm]
move - move an item up or down in the list [aliases: m]
clear - clear all completed items [aliases: cl]
clear-all - clear all items [aliases: ca]
help - print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
-h, --help Print help

# Path system

Use zero-indexed numbers to specify nested subtasks:

**Adding items:**

- `td add "task"` - adds to root level
- `td add 0 "subtask"` - adds subtask to first item
- `td add 0 1 "sub-subtask"` - adds subtask to second subtask of first item

**Other commands:**

- `td check 0` - marks first item as completed
- `td check 0 1` - marks second subtask of first item as completed
- `td delete 0` - deletes first item
- `td delete 0 1` - deletes second subtask of first item
- `td move 0 up` - moves first item up one position
- `td move 2 down` - moves third item down one position
- `td move 1 top` - moves second item to top
- `td move 3 bottom` - moves fourth item to bottom
- `td move 0 1 up` - moves second subtask of first item up
- `td move 2 0 2` - moves first subtask of third item to position 2
